      Narrowly-tailored measures taken by You to comply with applicable
      export control laws do not impose further restrictions.

   c) Derivative Works; Outbound GPL Compatibility

      If You distribute a Derivative Work, You must license the Derivative
      Work as a whole under this License, with prominent notice of such
      licensing. This condition may not be circumvented through such means
      as separate distribution of portions of the Derivative Work. You may
      additionally license the Derivative Work under the GPL, so that the
      recipient may further distribute the Derivative Work under either
      this License or the GPL.

   d) Object Code

      If Covered Code is in Object Code form, You must accompany the Object
      Code with a URL through which the Corresponding Source is made
      available, at no charge, by some standard or customary means of
      providing network access to source code.

      If you distribute the Object Code in a physical product or tangible
      storage medium ("Product"), the Corresponding Source must be
      available through such URL for two years from the date of Your most
      recent distribution of the Object Code in the Product. However, if
      the Product itself contains or is accompanied by the Corresponding
      Source (readily accessible to the Product user), You need not also
      comply with the preceding paragraph.

      Each recipient of Covered Code from You is an intended third-party
      beneficiary of this License solely as to this subsection
      2d, with the right to enforce its terms.

   e) Pass-Through

      When You distribute Covered Code, the recipient automatically
      receives a license to My Code from Me, subject to the terms of this
      License.

   Subsections 2a through 2d are conditions of this License.

